    <item>
      <title>What Do Bowflex PR3000 Home Gym Users Have To Say?</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/ICWkowpfQBs/what-do-bowflex-pr3000-home-gym-users.html</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 May 2012 10:17:16 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-vzQkMHesrWQ/T7-oxAVMJ6I/AAAAAAAABoY/jrR7HqiIUEg/s1600/Bowflex+PR3000+Home+Gym.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-vzQkMHesrWQ/T7-oxAVMJ6I/AAAAAAAABoY/jrR7HqiIUEg/s1600/Bowflex+PR3000+Home+Gym.jpg" /></a></div>
The <b>Bowflex PR3000 home gym</b> is a home gym with 210 lbs. of resistance that can be upgraded to 310<br />
&nbsp;lbs. for those looking for extra resistance when exercising. The gym has the capacity for over 50 strength and muscle building exercises. A built-in rowing station is included.<br />
<br />
The amount of resistance can be easily adjusted from as little as 5 lbs per exercise to as much as 210 lbs. You can workout your abs, arms, chest, back, shoulders, and lower body with this one exercise machine. 

<br />
<br />
<b><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001AS4YRQ/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001AS4YRQ">Find out how you can save up to 33% on a Bowflex PR3000 Home Gym at Amazon.</a></b><br />
<br />
<b></b><br />
<b><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B001AS4YRQ" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" /></b> <br />
<br />
<b>Adjustable Power Rods provide the resistance.</b> They have a number of advantages over weight plates used with land dumbbells.&nbsp; The resistance is more uniform across the exercise. The inertia that sometimes makes resistance uneven when using free weight is greatly diminished. The resistance is contained within the gym. You will not have weights cluttering up your workout space.<br />
<br />
Power Rods are made from a high-tech composite under quality control conditions. They are tested for quality and durability.<br />
<br />
<i>Tim</i>, from Indiana gets a great workout with his PR 3000 home gym.<br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<i>"I have had this product for a about 2 weeks now and have noticed a huge 
difference in the way I feel. I have lost 12 lbs. and am getting more 
toned everyday. I went to the gym several years ago, I feel like I did 
when I left the gym after each 20to 30 minute workout. I need to lose 
about 50 more lbs and am confident this product will get these results.</i><br />
<i><br /></i><br />
<i>I
 am glad I spent the extra money on the pr3000 instead of the pr1000. I 
think changing the cables between exercises would take alot more time. I
 highly recommend this product to anyone wanting to get in shape"</i> - from <a href="http://www.amazon.com/review/B001AS4YRQ/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;showViewpoints=1&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957" target="_blank">Amazon customer reviews.</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="https://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" /></blockquote>
<br />
<br />
<b>Other Features of the Bowflex PR3000 home gym.</b><br />
<ul>
<li>You can get in a complete, full body workout with the more than 50 exercises available from this single exercise platform. The exercises range from bench presses (standard, inclined, and declined) to leg exercises (squats, leg extensions, and hip abductors). You can see a more complete list of exercises <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001AS4YRQ/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001AS4YRQ">here.</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B001AS4YRQ" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" />&nbsp;</li>
<li>The space required to workout is minimal. An area of 9 feet by 7 feet is more than enough space to host the PR3000 gym.&nbsp;</li>
<li>The hand grips and ankle cuffs are multi-use. This adds flexibility to your workout which can lead to a boost in your performance.&nbsp;</li>
<li>The no change cable pulley system is a great time saver. It also boosts your performance by moving from exercise to exercise more efficiently.</li>
<li>The Bowflex PR3000 gym comes with 210 lbs. of resistance. If that's not enough for you just upgrade to 310 lbs.</li>
<li>The leg station lets you build up your legs with leg curls and extensions. The 4 inch cushioned rollers let you exercise in comfort.</li>
<li>&nbsp;The maximum user weight for this home gym is 300 lbs.</li>
</ul>
<i><b><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001AS4YRQ/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001AS4YRQ">Order the Bowflex PR3000 Home Gym from Amazon and Save.</a></b></i><br />
<br />
<b>What the men and women who already have the Bowflex PR3000 have to say.</b><br />
<br />
<br />
The PR3000 home gym frm Bowflex has been around for a while. It's been around long enough to garner a fair sampling of positive and negative reviews online. The good news is most all the reviews we found were positive.<br />
<br />
 <br />
We found 50 ( so far ) reviews at Amazon. You can read them for yourself <a href="http://www.amazon.com/review/B001AS4YRQ/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;showViewpoints=1&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957" target="_blank">here.</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="https://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" /> The overall combined rating was a very nice 4.4 stars out of a possible 5.0 star rating. The men and women who reviewed the PR3000 home gym mentioned that they liked the quick cable changes, the quietness of operation, and the fact that you can upgrade the resistance level .<br />
<br />
<i>Patti</i>, from Los Angeles, likes her Bowflex PR3000 home gym. She says it does everything she needs in a home gym. Even though Patti was originally in the market for a home gym using free weights, she eventually decided to go with the PR3000.<br />
<br />
She decide to go with this home gym over other mainly because it does not take up much floor space and also so she will not have to "move heavy weights around during my workout".<br />
<br />
Patti feels her new gym is very well made with attention paid to the details. She does wish it had a lat bar though. Overall, Patti, gave her new home gym a 4 star rating.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>Tim</i>, from Indiana, says he is "really glad" he spent the extra money and got the PR3000 instead of the PR1000 home gym. He's already lost some of the weight he wants to get rid of. He highly recommends this gym and says he feels like he did after a workout at the local gym.<br />
<br />
<i>Lain</i> is a busy mom and this is her first home gym. Looking for a gym that did not take up much space and was easy to use, Lain settled on the PR3000. She is happy with her choice.<br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<i>"The Bowflex PR3000 is perfect for those wishes.  I use it almost 
everyday and feel I get a great work out.  The machine is very well made
 and sturdy, and so easy to put together.  The Bowflex products are 
expensive, but well worth the money.  This home gym is a great 
alternative when going to a public gym is inconvienient."
      </i></blockquote>
</blockquote>
<i>Jason</i>, from Silicon Valley, was less satisfied. His beef is with the resistance. He feels the resistance is less than indicated and has upgraded but still has "maxed out on many exercises (like the bench press)". He says that is a shame because, "otherwise this is a really great machine."<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>Clay</i> is 6'3" and calls the Bowflex PR3000, "a perfect machine for me even." The kickbacks were a little awkward for Clay at first but be quickly got used to them. He say he'll "definitely" be upgrading to 310 lbs. soon. The ability to upgrade the resistance and the no pulley change system are big pluses in Clay's book. The no change pulley system not only saves him time but also lets him concentrate on the workouts.<br />
<br />
The Bowflex PR3000 was a perfect home gym for Bob and his wife.<br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
&nbsp;<i>"This machine is excellent. My wife and I have been using it for a month 
now and have seen an improvement in overall condition. We are both 
nearing 60 and wanted to do something to maintain our physical health. 
We have been very pleased.  It is very similar to the more expensive 
Xtreme® SE 2 home gym with the exception of the movable pulleys and 
small lat crunch bar.&nbsp;</i><br />
<br />
<i>I added the extra 100 lb. bow set and a pull down 
bar which I would recommend. The exercise illustrations are not as good 
or complete as those shown in the Xtreme manual. In fact you can follow 
most all of the exercises listed in the Xtreme SE2 manual." </i></blockquote>
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001AS4YRQ/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001AS4YRQ">Order the Bowflex PR3000 Home Gym from Amazon and Save.</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B001AS4YRQ" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" /><br />
<br />
We feel the Bowflex PR3000 is a well made, well thought out home gym that will meet the workout needs of many people. If you want to build your strength, tone up and tighten, or lose weight, this home gym will be an excellent tool to help you reach your goals.<br />
<br />
The main complaint we found was concerning the levels of resistance. Many people felt that the stated resistance levels were exaggerated. They felt the resistance was quite a bit less. So if you are planning on lifting heavy you'll probably want to either upgrade the resistance of choose another home gym.<br />
<br />
But overall is think this if a fine home gym that will meet the needs of most.&nbsp; <br />
<br />
<br /><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-6964410390112996487?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/jhFo8nwQ9p_O8buyA4YpqU-pk4s/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/jhFo8nwQ9p_O8buyA4YpqU-pk4s/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/jhFo8nwQ9p_O8buyA4YpqU-pk4s/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/jhFo8nwQ9p_O8buyA4YpqU-pk4s/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/ICWkowpfQBs" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
