    <item>
      <title>Biom by ECCO</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/Uf3HmuwZrq0/biom-by-ecco.html</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2012 13:33:48 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>What is the philosophy behind Biom by Ecco?</b><br />
<br />
Let's start at the beginning. That was 1963 when a Danish family based business started. The company that was started was dubbed Ecco. Their passion - their focus- was on the human foot.<br />
<br />
ECCO soon gained a reputation worldwide for comfort in the footwear they designed. Their focus on the foot give them a unique insight. Ecco found that the regular running shoes on the market confined feet. They wanted to support the foot's natural motion.<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/mn/search/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;field-keywords=ecco%20biom&amp;url=search-alias%3Dshoes&amp;sprefix=ecco%20biom%2Caps%2C200" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;" target="_blank"><img border="0" height="160" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-dvrRTz4iE2c/T6vQG6Cv4rI/AAAAAAAABlI/LHxOCK-O1bA/s320/biom.jpg" width="320" /></a></div>
<b>This led to the Biom Project.</b> The idea was profoundly simple - create a natural motion running shoe.<br />
<br />
<br />
World champion Triathlete Torbjorn Sindbale&nbsp; was involved in all phases of the development of the Biom project from the start. From the scientific background to the actual production, Trobjorn was there.<br />
<br />
He was involved in testing and research. He gave input into the concept and philosophy. <br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-vlkIQ9li1vA/T6vUbRAClyI/AAAAAAAABlU/JOCFSsaAZQ0/s1600/trobjorn.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-vlkIQ9li1vA/T6vUbRAClyI/AAAAAAAABlU/JOCFSsaAZQ0/s1600/trobjorn.jpg" /></a></div>
Torbjorn was initially somewhat skeptical. He had been running in motion control shoes and needed to run a full marathon in the Biom before he could fully believe in and use these shoes. <br />
<br />
He found out that "all the little things" he had experienced with muscles not being strong enough to handle the running load was not a thing of the past. He say his muscles developed again and got stronger due to the natural running motion his Ecco Biom running shoes allowed.<br />
<br />
<b>Trobjorn counsels patience. </b>He says it is going to take time transitioning from a motion control shoe to the natural motion of Biom. It will take some time, he says. But, over time, Biom running shoes are going to allow you to train at a higher level and see big performance gains.<br />
<br />
<b>Want better performance with natural motion? <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B003N8GQFY/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B003N8GQFY">Find out more or buy now at Amazon</a></b><br />
<br />
<br />
<b><br /></b><br />
Biom shoes by Ecco are not just for elite triathletes and distance runners. These natural motion shoes come in a variety of styles for women and men. There are Biom shoes for walking, hiking, and golfing as well.<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-bb_c9-KZ2b8/T6vZrkDtwoI/AAAAAAAABlg/5oCEFatZdpU/s1600/Ecco+Womens+Biom+1.2+walking+shoe.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="75" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-bb_c9-KZ2b8/T6vZrkDtwoI/AAAAAAAABlg/5oCEFatZdpU/s200/Ecco+Womens+Biom+1.2+walking+shoe.jpg" width="200" /></a></div>
Take, for instance, the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B003Y3FAL4/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B003Y3FAL4">ECCO Women's Biom Walk 1.2 Walking Shoe</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B003Y3FAL4" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" />.<br />
<br />
This is an excellent walking shoe that provides you with a very natural walking motion. The fit is snug and comfortable. They are lightweight, close to the ground, and offer good arch support.<br />
<br />
Here is what one lady from Greeneville, South Carolina had to say about her new walking shoes.<br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<i>" I wear these shoes every day.  I tried them on at the mall after wearing
 my "dress shoes" all day, and my feet and back went from achey and 
tired to feeling quite good, despite the fact that I'd been on my feet 
in uncomfortable shoes all day.  I have a low arch, and these shoes 
support it without pushing up on my foot too much.  My only complaint is
 that the cushioning has worn down a little faster than I'd like 
(especially given the price), but they're still in very good condition.<br /><br />These
 are definitely shoes to try on before you buy; that's a big chunk of 
money, and it sounds like this shoe is particularly good for my foot 
shape as opposed to others'."&nbsp; </i>- <a href="http://www.eccousa.com/shoes/biom/womens/walking/womens-biom-walk-textile-1.2/2532/detail.aspx#ReviewHeader" target="_blank">from Ecco Customer reviews</a>.</blockquote>
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004VBBHKG/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004VBBHKG">ECCO Men's Biom Walk 1.1 Walking Shoes</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B004VBBHKG" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" width="1" /> were called "the best shoes I've ever owned." by one happy customer. Read what Briany had to say.<br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
&nbsp;"<i>I don't review many products, but I had to share my experience with this
 shoe.  I am on my feet a lot at work, and looked at this shoe because I
 have found Ecco dress shoes to be the most comfortable.  Well, this 
walking shoe has put every other shoe I've ever owned to the test.  It 
literally feels like putting a glove on my foot, and with a Walking 
Company orthotic to correct my overpronation, I may never wear another 
shoe again.  The price is high, no doubt about it, but I have a hard 
time finding comfortable shoes, and Ecco seems to have the right last 
for my feet.  The science behind the Biom thing is beyond me, all I can 
say is it works.  I can't say they would be right for everbody, but for 
me, this is now the gold standard shoe that all others I wear have to 
compare.<br /><br />I will be curious to see if the leather and construction
 is as durable as they advertise, but the yak leather feels very 
luxurious.  If they break down too soon, I will amend this review."</i></blockquote>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004VBBHKG/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004VBBHKG" target="_blank"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-fbFnlXShlgw/T6vhUNALjzI/AAAAAAAABls/TqlXYwHA1LE/s320/ecco+biom+mens+1.1.jpg" width="215" /></a></div>
<br />
<br />
David pretty much agrees.&nbsp; <i></i><br />
<i><br /></i><br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<i>"I did a lot of research on top shoe brands and ECCO is one of the best. 
It's not consistently the top brand by most reviewers, but they 
definitely offer the most attractive shoe designs out of the top brands.
 I work in retail so I'm on my feet a lot and I wanted to go for a super
 comfortable shoe. When you first put this shoe on, it feels like a 
slightly better than average walking shoe, but you don't really notice 
how great of a shoe this is until you start putting a little weight on 
the feet by hopping or lightly jogging. This shoe being made of yak 
leather is said to be 5x stronger than regular leather so I hopefully 
will be enjoying the comfort of this shoe for many years to come. So 
perhaps dishing out the extra dollars for this will be worth it in the 
long run (no pun intended).<br /><br />UPDATE 10/19/11: This is an awesome 
walking shoe. And that's what this shoe should be used for. Walking. I 
tried jogging in them for a short distance before and they're okay for 
that, but they get a little uncomfortable. I don't believe the shoe 
insert was made to handle jogging so I would recommend buying inserts if
 you want to use these shoes for that. But with that said I'll stick to a
 pair of cross training shoes for my exercising. These shoes are still 
as comfortable as the day I got them. Anytime I know I'll be doing a lot
 of standing or walking, I'm always sure to put these on before I go out
 the door.<br /><br />On a side note: I got this in beige. It keeps clean 
well and and I get a lot of compliments. Its an attractive looking shoe 
and there's really nothing out there like it."</i></blockquote>
<br />
We found 5 customer reviews for these shoes at Amazon. Each one gave the Men's Ecco Biom 1.1 Walking Shoes a full 5 star grade. You can see the latest reviews and ratings <a href="http://www.amazon.com/review/B004VBBHKG/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;showViewpoints=1&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957" target="_blank">here.</a><br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4pM5fRP6D7w/T7DmZUEO5ZI/AAAAAAAABmI/VoAi6l-t9nA/s1600/ecco+biom+hydromax.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4pM5fRP6D7w/T7DmZUEO5ZI/AAAAAAAABmI/VoAi6l-t9nA/s1600/ecco+biom+hydromax.jpg" /></a></div>
Golf Shoes have also received the Biom treatment.<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B005GBWCVS/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B005GBWCVS"> ECCO Men's BIOM Hydromax Golf Shoes</a><br />
are an expensive but very comfortable choice - especially amongst golfers who like to walk the course. Here's one New York golfer's opinion of these shoes.<br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<i>&nbsp;"I've played for 15 years and usually walk.  These saved my feet.  Super comfortable.  The best I've ever worn.<br /><br />I
 used to buy cheap shoes and buy new ones more often.  Wrong.  Invest 
money on these shoes.  It is worth twice the price.  You have to try on 
any shoe but you'll see as soon as you put these on"
      </i></blockquote>
<br />
Cross training shoes like the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B003Y3FALO/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B003Y3FALO">ECCO Women's Biom Train 1.2 Cross-Training Shoe</a> offer a lightweight and comfortable shoe that is versatile enough for a variety of activities. In addition to their comfort and lightness, customers also say they are attractive, durable, and provide good arch support.<br />
<br />
<i>Melari</i> thinks they are a great looking shoe that she can wear anywhere. <i>"I really liked the appearance.  I took these shoes with me to London, 
and walked everywhere.  They were comfortable.  I did try using them in 
my kickboxing class, and I felt I needed a bit more cushion for that 
type of activity.  Otherwise, it's a great shoe."</i><br />
<br />
<i>( 215 )&nbsp;</i><br />
<br />
If you are searching for a comfortable, lightweight shoe that gives you a natural running motion,<i>&nbsp; </i>Biom by Ecco offers shoes in many different styles for sports and everyday life.<br />
<br />
<i></i><br />
******

<b>&nbsp;</b><br />
<br />
<b>Related:</b><br />
<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.squidoo.com/asics-kinsei" target="_blank">Asics Kinsei 4 Running Shoes&nbsp;</a><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.squidoo.com/asics-cumulus" target="_blank">Asics Cumulus 13 Running Shoes</a><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-7027416349118531300?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/Cl0Uo6lUzMuAih6Gbc-ZCqKN-3I/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/Cl0Uo6lUzMuAih6Gbc-ZCqKN-3I/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/Cl0Uo6lUzMuAih6Gbc-ZCqKN-3I/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/Cl0Uo6lUzMuAih6Gbc-ZCqKN-3I/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/Uf3HmuwZrq0" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
