    <item>
      <title>New Balance Women's WT20v1 Trail Minimus Shoes</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/yX844WBlE1U/new-balance-womens-wt20v1-trail-minimus.html</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 01 May 2012 23:22:39 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><b style="font-weight: normal; line-height: 1em;">Take a different approach to trail running. New Balance Trail Minimus shoes for women and men have the durable yet lightweight Minimal Vibram® and a fitted, very minimalist upper. These two items combine for a shoe lets you experience trail with a nearly barefoot experience.

The drop from heel to toe is only about a third of what you would expect from traditional running shoes. The superior light weight foam used in the mid-sole is exceptionally durable. It is 12% lighter than conventional foam yet this highly engineered foam resists compression set.

All this technology works together to give you a trail shoe you can use with or without shoes to gain a comfortable and enjoyable near barefoot running experience. </b></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;">New Balance Women's WT20v1 Trail Minimus Shoes</span><br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-Z1gbup7FLI0/T6BwLa6o3dI/AAAAAAAABkQ/KyjxKkXLGlw/s1600/nb+minimus+trail.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="140" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-Z1gbup7FLI0/T6BwLa6o3dI/AAAAAAAABkQ/KyjxKkXLGlw/s320/nb+minimus+trail.jpg" width="320" /></a></div>
</div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004KZP678/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004KZP678">New Balance Women's WT20v1 Trail Minimus Shoes</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B004KZP678" style="border: medium none ! important; margin: 0px ! important;" width="1" />
 approach trail running differently than traditional running shoes. Imagine combining the durability of the Vibram® outsole with a fitted minimalist upper.

With a modified upper on the same sole as the WT10, these Trail Minimus shoes give you a near barefoot experience, with or without socks.

<b>So, what do women that have already purchased a pair of these shoes think of them?</b>&nbsp;</span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;">We found <a href="http://www.amazon.com/review/B004KZP678/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;showViewpoints=1&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957" target="_blank">dozens of written reviews</a><img alt="" border="0" height="1" src="https://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" style="border: medium none ! important; margin: 0px ! important;" width="1" /> online. The overwhelming rating for these shoes was positive. They scored an impressive 4.6 out of 5 stars. Here are the highlighted stories of several women that have already bought a pair of New Balance Trail Minimus shoes for themselves.&nbsp;</span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;<i>Ace</i> had owned several pairs of New Balance shoes before. In addition, she had over the years also owned Pumas, Converse, and Nike shoes. Ace tells us - <i>" ... but NONE even come close to the New Balance WT20 Trail Minimus shoes. </i> She likes that they are very lightweight without compromising durability or support.

The traction is "pretty nice", says Ace. She purchased the shoe in WIDE and is glad she did.&nbsp;</span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;">The only drawback as Ace sees it is the limited choice in colors. She wishes New Balance offered more! She's how Ace sums it up.

<i>" ...So...If you're looking for a shoe that is both good looking AND comfortable, I recommend you give these a try. My sister doesn't even like sneakers and after seeing mine she's thinking of getting herself a pair in black and pink. If you suffer from chronic foot/ankle pain like me, you'll be pleasantly surprised at how supportive and yet comfortable these shoes are. Pardon the trite expression but you'll feel like you're walking on air. =D

Bottom line: An awesome shoe!!! '</i>

<i>&nbsp;</i></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><i>Diane</i> suggests you " ... take it slowly and use these shoes for off road.". She suggests using the Trail Minimus shoes in conjunction with regular running shoes in order to give your muscles plenty of time to adjust. She says her shoes are comfortable and light. They fit her narrow feet well and " snuggly:)".

<i>&nbsp;</i></span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<span style="font-size: small;"><i>Lacey</i> tells us her New Balance Trail Minimus running shoes, " ...CHANGED MY LIFE..." After suffering from bad knees and shin splints for years, she was researching barefoot running. Lacey discovered several cases of "improving knee pain and shin splints due to the foot not being on an incline like so many other shoes do in the heel."

At first Lacey tried five finger running shoes.&nbsp;</span></div>
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
<br /></div>
<span style="font-size: small;">These were not a good fit for her however and the specialty shop where she bought her five finger shoes suggested she try the Trail Minimus shoes. It turned out to be a great buy as Lacey writes.

<i>&nbsp;</i></span><br />
<br />
<blockquote class="tr_bq">
<span style="font-size: small;"><i>" ...I run in these nearly everyday, on a treadmill and outdoors. Great traction, really light feeling, excellent flexibility and most of all I have minor to no knee pain and my shin splints have disappeared. And unlike the five-finger I did not feel the need to spend several weeks working my way into them. I do suggest wearing a lighter/thinner sock with them as they are very light themselves, thicker socks make them feel stiff. I am thinking about buying a second pair just in case they stop making them. Even though my shoes look nearly brand new after 8 months of running 3-6 times a week. Great Buy!!!! "</i></span></blockquote>
<br />
<div style="font-family: Georgia,&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;">
</div><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-7039209192333104874?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/k87xoXSI8FGvbVWpPNmUsi2jjgE/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/k87xoXSI8FGvbVWpPNmUsi2jjgE/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/k87xoXSI8FGvbVWpPNmUsi2jjgE/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/k87xoXSI8FGvbVWpPNmUsi2jjgE/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/yX844WBlE1U" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/home-exercise-equipment-reviews-and-tips/Home_Exercise_Equipment_Reviews_And_Tips-New_Balance_Womens_WT20v1_Trail_Minimus_Shoes.mp3" length="2127306" type="audio/mpeg" />
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Is It Okay For an Athlete to Do P90X?</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/04t1ximcKoQ/is-it-okay-for-athlete-to-do-p90x.html</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Apr 2012 16:35:25 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[A reader, who plays baseball, asks if it is okay for an athlete to do P90X?<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Z8Nas0_5M14/T5rHuICJ_7I/AAAAAAAABkE/NI1kSIH2MPI/s1600/baseball+player.png" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="200" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Z8Nas0_5M14/T5rHuICJ_7I/AAAAAAAABkE/NI1kSIH2MPI/s200/baseball+player.png" width="180" /></a></div>
The answer is : P90X makes a great workout for most anyone that is already in pretty good physical fitness. Many athletes - even professional athletes - are incorporating P90X into their training. <br />
<br />
With workout ranging from plyometrics to yoga to strength building and cardiovascular health, P90X improves athletic and everyday performance. <br />
<br />
Athletes need flexibility, strength, the ability to move powerfully and athletically. They need strength, balance, and endurance. Believe me, P90X addresses all of these.<br />
<br />
<b>A well thought out nutrition plan is included as well.</b> With the P90X program you can go at it as hard or as easy as you need to. It is infinitely flexible in that way. You can continue using and modifying the program long after the initial 90 days. I've been using, enjoying, and benefiting my P90X DVDs for years. <br />
<br />
I guess I'm still an athlete of sorts ( 54 years old and play golf regularly). But whether you are a high school or college athletic or play professionally, I say you can get something out of P90X. <br />
<br />
<b><a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/X2-Base?referringRepId=38076%20">Learn more or purchase P90X directly from Team Beachbody here.</a></b><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-7138437483762663782?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/1lNfCSO0zzSv2msZDpcL3Hqcp1Y/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/1lNfCSO0zzSv2msZDpcL3Hqcp1Y/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/1lNfCSO0zzSv2msZDpcL3Hqcp1Y/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/1lNfCSO0zzSv2msZDpcL3Hqcp1Y/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/04t1ximcKoQ" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/home-exercise-equipment-reviews-and-tips/Home_Exercise_Equipment_Reviews_And_Tips-Is_It_Okay_For_an_Athlete_to_Do_P90X.mp3" length="751869" type="audio/mpeg" />
    </item>
