      <title>How Many Calories Can I Burn During a P90X Workout?</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/w2asgUjdp3Y/how-many-calories-can-i-burn-during.html</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 05 Apr 2012 17:42:31 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align: center;">
<img border="0" height="200" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-LGpJHv5B3os/T322yWpw_gI/AAAAAAAABiU/5L1zYWgiBQA/s200/P90X-Stretch-Workout.jpg" width="199" /></div>
<br />
Is P90X an effective way to burn calories? Just how many calories can I expect to burn during a P90X workout?<br />
<br />
A P90X workout is an effective way to burn calories and working out six day a week with this program is bound to help you burn off calories. It is just impossible to give you a highly accurate forecast to how many calories you can expect to shed.<br />
<br />
That said, we found an estimate of <b>700 calories per workout</b> on the P90X message boards. You can go to that discussion <a href="http://www.teambeachbody.com/connect/message-boards/-/message_boards/message/19575649" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">here</a>. <br />
<br />
I would imagine that 700 calories per workout is at the high end of the spectrum. Of course how many calories you or I shed depends on our fitness level, workout intensity, and many other factors. P90X is not a weight loss program but many people report losing weight during by using the program. This is all the more impressive when you consider they probably increased their lean body mass so the loss in weight was more likely to be permanent.<br />
<br />
The bottom line is that P90X is a highly effective extreme fitness program for many people. If you are ready to get into tip top shape - the best of your life - it's a real good program to take you there.<br />
