      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/kCchyZfe82Y/whats-equipment-needed-for-p90x.html</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 15 Mar 2012 17:48:58 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-OU-aunE4CEI/T2IJDvx_7BI/AAAAAAAABhQ/gtyM6SjLtEw/s1600/P90X-Equipment.png"><img style="float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 250px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-OU-aunE4CEI/T2IJDvx_7BI/AAAAAAAABhQ/gtyM6SjLtEw/s400/P90X-Equipment.png" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5720144436684385298" border="0" /></a><br />The <span style="font-weight: bold;">equipment needed for P90X according to the fitness guide</span> of the P90X package includes a chin up bar, resistance bands and/or dumbbells, a heart rate monitor, and push up bars. They also list a yoga mat, yoga blocks and a body fat tester.<br /><br />While the more of these items you have in your home gym the better, many of us started out without the complete group and added items each time through the program.<br /><br />Having a <span style="font-weight: bold;">good set of resistance bands</span> is a must. The <a style="font-weight: bold;" href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/BLINEBandKits?referringRepId=38076">B Lines resistance bands</a> are perfect for P90X. This kit has color coded resistance bands at different levels of resistance. There are 2 resistance bands plus an additional free band included with the kit. It also comes with 2 sets of handles with comfort grips.<br /><br />With resistance bands you can burn fat and tone lean muscle. Because they are portable and convenient you can take them with you when you are on the more. These resistance bands are especially popular among women.<br /><br /><a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/ChinUpBar?referringRepId=38076"><img style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 250px; height: 250px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nip9ZMa6-T4/T2INiHBxYnI/AAAAAAAABhc/YJjZChNr-vU/s320/p90x%2Bchin%2Bup%2Bbar.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5720149356367143538" border="0" /></a>A reliable and safe pull up bar, like the <a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/ChinUpBar?referringRepId=38076"><span style="font-weight: bold;">P90X Chin Up Bar</span> </a>will help you develop and strengthen the muscle groups of the upper back as well as you shoulders and arms.<br /><br />It really made a difference in my results when I got this chin up bar. Things I like about it include the fact that you can do chin ups and pull ups from multiple positions with this bar. It has a 300 lb. maximum user capacity and it removes and attaches easily to the door that I use.<br /><br />The P90X Chin Up bar is made of heavy gauge steel. The doorway you use it with needs to be sturdy and must have the border trim. It fits doorways up to 32 inches wide. The minimum door width is 5 inches. The max is 6.5 inches.<br /><br /><br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001ARYU58/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001ARYU58"><img style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 300px; height: 300px;" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-sfhQo0pxAcA/T2IWyAU15FI/AAAAAAAABho/KYlXJcT-vfs/s320/bowflex%2Bselecttech.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5720159525050639442" border="0" /></a>Weight resistance exercise to build strength and muscle make up a large portion of P90X. Depending on your level of fitness - and your fitness goals - you will need either a good set of dumbbells or a set of resistance bands. If you want to build muscle, it is recommended you have a set of dumbbells at the ready.<br /><br />A set of adjustable dumbbells, like the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001ARYU58/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001ARYU58"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Bowflex Selecttech dumbbells</span></a> allow you to quickly adjust the amount of weight as you move from exercise to exercise. In addition they are designed to keep your workout space uncluttered. A set of these dumbbells is like having pairs of dumbbells in one.<br /><br />A good <a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/mn/search/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;field-keywords=heart%20rate%20monitor&amp;url=search-alias%3Dsporting&amp;sprefix=heart%20rate%20monitor%2Csporting%2C199">heart rate monitor</a><img src="https://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" alt="" style="border:none !important; margin:0px !important;" border="0" height="1" width="1" /> lets you measure the intensity and progress you are making. This is a must have when you are engaged in an extreme fitness program.<br /><br />Yoga in an important part of P90X. While the yoga workout included in P90X is undoubtedly intense - especially if you have never done much yoga- the benefits are undeniable. Your progress will be even more impressive with the right yoga mat and a good pair of yoga blocks.<br /><br /><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-o4_sC0QlXCI/T2InbLXbyMI/AAAAAAAABh0/ZzFoCqDQNlk/s1600/yoga%2Bblocks.jpg"><img style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 300px; height: 300px;" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-o4_sC0QlXCI/T2InbLXbyMI/AAAAAAAABh0/ZzFoCqDQNlk/s320/yoga%2Bblocks.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5720177824574982338" border="0" /></a>The <a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/yogaMat?referringRepId=38076">Yoga Mat</a> from Beachbody is a thick, textured sticky mat that stabilizes your yoga and lets you concentrate on things like proper alignment and balance. It measures 24" by 68" and is hand washable.<br /><br />The <a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/MDACCYBLOCK2101?referringRepId=38076">Yoga Block</a> set has 2 blocks that are great for assisting you as you work to deepen postures and they also can stabilize your posture in poses that are difficult for you. Each yoga block measures 4" by 6" by 9".<br /><br /><br />Push up bars are great for getting a larger range of motion when doing your push ups. It is also more comfortable to do pushups with these - especially if you have wrist problems like me.<br /><br />I prefer the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000KDM3BG/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B000KDM3BG">Perfect Push Up </a>set. They are durable and comfortable. They also turn and let you move your arms in a more natural motion.<br /><br />The P90X guide also mentions a body fat tester. Since my scale has a somewhat accurate percent body fat measurement, I just use that. Here is the link for the <a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/MDACCBODFATK2?referringRepId=38076">Body Fat Tester</a> in case you are interested.<br /><br />As I mentioned earlier in this article, while you can get all of this equipment at once you don't have to. I add to my fitness equipment as time goes by. After going through P90X for a while, you'll get a sense of just what your workouts need to give you a boost in performance.<br /><br />******<br /><br />Related: <a href="http://www.squidoo.com/equipment-for-p90x">Equipment for P90X</a><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-7622713363779274335?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/3tfaQdRBjyRyUPcShpMN5nio8wk/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/3tfaQdRBjyRyUPcShpMN5nio8wk/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/3tfaQdRBjyRyUPcShpMN5nio8wk/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/3tfaQdRBjyRyUPcShpMN5nio8wk/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/kCchyZfe82Y" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
