      <title>Body Max IT6000 Inversion Therapy Table Review</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/VzvaiqHRwf4/body-max-it6000-inversion-therapy-table.html</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 10 Feb 2012 12:08:16 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-lnRy8NtbKrc/TzRFuUanDhI/AAAAAAAABfE/svguGhxJJV0/s1600/Body%2BMax%2BIT6000%2BInversion%2BTherapy%2BTable.jpg"><img style="float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 300px; height: 300px;" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-lnRy8NtbKrc/TzRFuUanDhI/AAAAAAAABfE/svguGhxJJV0/s320/Body%2BMax%2BIT6000%2BInversion%2BTherapy%2BTable.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5707263289841880594" border="0" /></a><br />The <span style="font-weight: bold;">Body Max IT6000 Inversion Therapy Table</span> is an easy to adjust, deluxe dual pin home inversion table.<br /><br />This is a budget priced inversion therapy table that has received very good reviews from customers. In fact, it got a <span style="font-weight: bold;">4.4 star rating out of a possible full 5 stars</span> when we combined 138 customer reviews submitted at Amazon. That is a very high rating for a economical inversion table.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001O2SRGM/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001O2SRGM">Check out the price and reviews at Amazon.com.</a><br /><br />We found reviewer after reviewer writing about how sturdy the Body Max IT6000 Inversion Therapy Table is. Here is how one reviewer,<span style="font-style: italic;"> T. Adams</span>, put it.<br /><br /><blockquote style="font-style: italic;">"Knowing these things can run upwards of $300-400 I was expecting  something of less quality when I ordered this $119.00 unit.  I am  pleasantly surprised with the sturdiness and construction of this table.   I would recommend it to all my family and friends."</blockquote><br /><br />Most folks thought assembling this inversion table was fairly easy and straightforward. Some encountered problems however.<br /><br /><span style="font-style: italic;"></span><blockquote><span style="font-style: italic;">"Assembling this table looked a bit daunting at first, especially since  they recommend you assemble it with two people.  However, with a little  patience and `alone', I had it together in less than an hour. ..."</span><br style="font-style: italic;"><br style="font-style: italic;"><span style="font-style: italic;">"I was looking for back relief for a reasonable price. Researched lots of  products, mainly based on customer feedback, so here's mine; Value=A+!  Very sturdy. The hardware for assembly was a drawback. Missing a couple  pieces,(couple nuts &amp; a bolt); went to the local hardware store  &amp; bought new ones to avoid returning the whole thing. ..."</span></blockquote>But the overwhelming sentiment we gleaned from the reviews was a sense of  satisfaction with a sturdy piece of home exercise equipment that does it's job. They reported that the Body Max IT6000 gave relief from the various pains and discomforts they were experiencing.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001O2SRGM/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001O2SRGM">Learn more or buy now at Amazon.</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">Body Max IT6000 Inversion Therapy Table Features and Specs.</span><br /><ul><li>It features a deluxe dual pin adjustment system. This system allows you to adjust your Body Max IT6000 to accommodate user heights anywhere from 4'8" to 6' 3".</li><li>A 250 lb. weight capacity.</li><li>Easy ankle adjustments with the lower spring loaded pull pin.</li><li>A safety strap that lets you control the amount of inversion.</li><li>A safety lock to keep the table secure.</li><li>U shaped hand rails to make your movements easy and secure.</li><li>Folds up so you can store it or take your therapy table with you when on the go.</li></ul><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">In conclusion.</span> If you want a sturdy basic inversion table for use in the home and do not want to pay a lot more for fancy bells and whistles, the Body Max IT6000 is an excellent choice. They are built well and have the features you need at a very reasonable cost. </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-1350273738860614978?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/2Zef9SaB9u4V5dYvt2wAXhIc2DQ/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/2Zef9SaB9u4V5dYvt2wAXhIc2DQ/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/2Zef9SaB9u4V5dYvt2wAXhIc2DQ/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/2Zef9SaB9u4V5dYvt2wAXhIc2DQ/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/VzvaiqHRwf4" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/home-exercise-equipment-reviews-and-tips/Home_Exercise_Equipment_Reviews_And_Tips-Body_Max_IT6000_Inversion_Therapy_Table_Review.mp3" length="1564837" type="audio/mpeg" />
