      <title>Can I Lose Weight with P90X ?</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/JAxERs1NJ4I/can-i-lose-weight-with-p90x.html</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Feb 2012 22:12:54 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/P90X?referringRepId=38076"><img style="float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 200px; height: 158px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-U6ongzodpd8/TzLTSnrSglI/AAAAAAAABe4/PRUTXJ7LIFg/s200/p90x%2Blean.gif" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5706855994673496658" border="0" /></a><br />Steve Edwards answers the 'losing weight with P90x' question in an informative article at <a href="http://www.teambeachbody.com/get-fit/fitness-tip/-/ftip/16422/all/93/75">TeamBeachbody.com</a>. Steve states that,<br /><blockquote style="font-style: italic;"><br />"P90X is not a weight loss program, yet most people lose weight by doing  it. This is because most of those people begin the program with more  body fat than they're happy with, and getting ripped means they've lost  body fat and weight. But some people want more. They want nothing but to  be lean. ..."</blockquote><br /><br />Then he goes on to point out that the lean and doubles plans are designed with weight loss more in mind than the classic P90x schedule. But, he notes, <span style="font-style: italic;">"... losing weight has a lot more to do with how you do the program than which option you choose."</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">The Key to Getting Lean</span><br /><br />He suggests that if you want to become lean begin with the lean program and then progress to the doubles program. To further modify your program for maximhttp://www.blogger.com/img/blank.gifum ( lean ) results, Steve suggest lighter weight and more reps. The key is to use enough weight to fail at the end of each set.<br /><br />If getting lean is your fitness goal, the <a href="http://teambeachbody.com/shop/-/shopping/P90X?referringRepId=38076">P90X Fitness Program</a> can get you there. Be sure to check out Steve's informative article for maximum results.<br /><br />Related:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.squidoo.com/p90x-review">P90X Review - Learn The Facts</a><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-3734385296841258464?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/oXLrYpFaVaqfkFjqlecKzD8ww0M/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/oXLrYpFaVaqfkFjqlecKzD8ww0M/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/oXLrYpFaVaqfkFjqlecKzD8ww0M/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/oXLrYpFaVaqfkFjqlecKzD8ww0M/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/JAxERs1NJ4I" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/home-exercise-equipment-reviews-and-tips/Home_Exercise_Equipment_Reviews_And_Tips-Can_I_Lose_Weight_with_P90X_.mp3" length="782631" type="audio/mpeg" />
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Concept2 Model D Indoor Rowing Machine Review</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~3/l4o2OttLxIc/concept2-model-d-indoor-rowing-machine.html</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 Feb 2012 17:16:55 GMT</pubDate>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001A0ZT2I/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001A0ZT2I"><img style="float:left; margin:0 10px 10px 0;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 300px; height: 300px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-XcJT0Qm4qF4/TywB7z1XttI/AAAAAAAABeg/dvojV1e7I_o/s400/Concept2%2BModel%2BD%2BIndoor%2BRowing%2BMachine.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5704936955009545938" border="0" /></a><br />The <span style="font-weight: bold;">Concept2 Model D Indoor Rowing Machine</span> is known as the world's best rowing machine. It is very highly rated by purchasers of this exercise machine.<br /><br />The Concept2 Indoor Rower gives you a total body cardio workout. Men and women use the Concept2 to stay in top shape and lose weight. They cross train for other sports and even use this indoor rower to train for rowing on the water.<br /><br />This is a well designed, well made indoor rower that is<span style="font-weight: bold;"> built to last</span>. One rower that uses his Concept2 rower 5 to 6 times a week for an average of 45 minutes per session has this to say about the durability of his rower. <span style="font-style: italic;">" ... I still use the rower and it is still in PERFECT condition! The seat is a bit softer but no wear or tear... "</span><br /><br /><br /><a style="font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001A0ZT2I/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001A0ZT2I">Find out more about the Concept2 Indoor Rower and buy now at Amazon.</a><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">The sliding seat compresses and extends your legs with each stroke.</span> With a large range of motion for both the legs and the arms, strength and flexibility are enhanced. The abdominal and back muscles also get involved with the row. In short, you exercise your total body rowing this way.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">Low impact, rhythmic exercise is easy on your joints. </span>Not only will rowing engage the major muscle groups - and burn a load of calories - it is also a great way to relieve stress.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">More features of the Concept2 Model D Indoor rower.</span><br /><ul><li>The flywheel is quiet and designed to minimize noise. It also gives you a smooth feel - like rowing on the water - as you exercise.</li><br /><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-WFThMkJkXS4/TywQMNQS4PI/AAAAAAAABes/gRAFsMK8eDs/s1600/PM3.jpg"><img style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 212px; height: 298px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-WFThMkJkXS4/TywQMNQS4PI/AAAAAAAABes/gRAFsMK8eDs/s320/PM3.jpg" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5704952629874057458" border="0" /></a><li>The PM3 performance monitor keeps track of these workout metrics - distance, speed, pace, and calories. When you begin to row, the PM3 turns on and begins to give you feedback. You will not need to push a button to get it started. It has <b>Five display options:</b> All data, force curve, rowing with a pace boat, bar chart and even large print.   </li><li>The handle is ergonomically designed for your comfort. It allows natural positioning for your arms and hands.</li><li>The aluminum rail is capped with stainless steel to give smooth seat movement while rowing.</li><li>The foot-flex footrest are adjustable for added comfort.</li><li>With an optional Polar receiver ( sold separately) you can monitor your heart rate.</li><li>Caster wheels are built in so you can move the rower around easily.</li><li>The user weight capacity is 500 lbs.</li><li>When in use the Concept2 Model D has a footprint of 9 feet by 4 feet.</li><li>For storage and easy mobility the rower can collapse.</li></ul><p><a style="font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001A0ZT2I/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001A0ZT2I">Get further details and buy now at Amazon.</a></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Customer reviews and ratings for the Concept2 Model D Indoor Rowing Machine.</span></p><p>So... how do the men and women that have already purchased - and use - "The World Best Rowing Machine" feel about their purchase? Are they satisfied and getting the results they want? Is their rower holding up to heavy use? Are there any unforeseen problems or issues they have uncovered?</p><p>Researching customer reviews give us an unrivaled way to quickly get an accurate and unbiased account of any product we are considering buying online. We can learn of any problems others have experienced or have our concerns answered.<br /></p><p>Fortunately, there are a great number of written customer reviews on the Concept2 Model D Indoor rowing machine available at the Amazon customer review section. (There were 161 reviews at the time of this report.)</p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">The cumulative rating of these reviews was an amazing 4.9 out of a possible 5 stars!</span> There is a treasure of information that anyone investigating this indoor rower would find very useful in the written reports supplied by these women and men. <a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/review/B001A0ZT2I/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;showViewpoints=1&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957">Read all the reviews here</a><img src="https://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=folthenewyory-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" alt="" style="border:none !important; margin:0px !important;" border="0" height="1" width="1" /><br /></p><p>One review points to the Concept2 Model D rower is instrumental in a 75 pound weight loss. </p><p><span style="font-style: italic;"></span></p><blockquote><span style="font-style: italic;">" ... I utilize this machine, along with a low carb diet and walking 3-4 miles  2 to 3 times a week, to lose 75 pounds! I started this last September  2008- weighing in at nearly 300 pounds at 6'1".  As of now, end of March  2009, I am down to 225 and feel great!  That's it, no magic other than  consistency! If it were not for this rower, my efforts would have been  much, much less successful. .. "</span></blockquote><br /><br />Another reviewer considers her purchase of the Concept2 rower as an investment.<br /><br /><span style="font-style: italic;"></span><blockquote><span style="font-style: italic;">'The Concept2 Indoor Rowing Machine is the universal standard for quality  rowing machines. If you want to perform this indoor exercise correctly,  this is the machine to use. If you visit any high school, college, or  club rowing program you will find Concept2 rowing machines are likely  the only rowing machines they use. It is good for sweep rowers and  scullers, gives you lots of workout feedback, and requires very little  maintenance. </span><br style="font-style: italic;"><br style="font-style: italic;"><span style="font-style: italic;">My model D has over 2,000,000 meters on it and neither of  us show any sign of slowing down. Older, used Model A, B, and C indoor  rowers still retain their value, work well, and have faithful and  dedicated users. If you're going to purchase an indoor rower, make an  investment for the long-term because this machine (or the Model E) is  the only one to consider."</span><br style="font-style: italic;"></blockquote><br />One reviewer points out that the Concept2 rower is "not just for elite athletes". A self described, "dumpy, middle aged woman" with a hip replacement, <span style="font-style: italic;">M.Ricky</span> say she can recommend this rowing machine without reservation.<br /><br /><span style="font-style: italic;"></span><blockquote><span style="font-style: italic;">"  ... I spent the first week focusing on correct technique and not killing  myself.  The machine comes with two booklets, a memory card, and a  bottle of chain oil.  The Indoor Rowing booklet has a lot of good  information on proper form and suggested workouts starting from your  very first day.  </span><br style="font-style: italic;"><br style="font-style: italic;"><span style="font-style: italic;">There are also videos and active user forums on the  Concept2 website.  I've been following the suggestions, started slowly,  set the damper at 3 and have left it there.  Most nights I row from 25  to 40 minutes followed by stretching (recommended: AM/PM Stretch with  Madeleine Lewis or AM Yoga for Your Week with Rodney Yee). </span><br style="font-style: italic;"><br style="font-style: italic;"><span style="font-style: italic;">I spent a  lot of time on form and kept my stroke rate at about 18-19 spm.  Slow,  right?  But I don't get sloppy and as I get stronger it seems that  upping the stroke rate doesn't really improve my performance all that  much.  </span><br style="font-style: italic;"><br style="font-style: italic;"><span style="font-style: italic;">Before I started rowing, the morning routine was to get out of  bed with cramping in my thigh and buttocks that nearly put me in tears.   No joke: this disappeared overnight as soon as I started rowing.  I  felt a little soreness, mostly in my upper back, but zero lower back  pain and no cramping AT ALL.  One week of this was worth the $900. "</span></blockquote><br />Again, the customer reviews are almost universal in their praise of the Concept2 Model D Indoor Rowing machine. They not only praise the rowers utility and smoothness but also point to it's durability.<br /><br />The Concept2 is currently in stock at Amazon and can be delivered via Standard Shipping.<br /><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B001A0ZT2I/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=folthenewyory-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B001A0ZT2I">Buy the Concept2 at Amazon. </a><br /><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><br /><div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">A Comparison of the Concept2 Model D and Model E Indoor Rowers</span><br /><br />Not sure whether the Model D or Model E is right for you? This quick video featuring Will Spaulding of the customer service team at <span style="font-weight: bold;">Concept2 </span>explains the differences between their Model D and Model E.<br /><br /><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/tYODJYq2XEA?rel=0" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" width="560"></iframe><br /><br /><br /><iframe src="http://rcm.amazon.com/e/cm?lt1=_blank&amp;bc1=000000&amp;IS2=1&amp;bg1=FFFFFF&amp;fc1=000000&amp;lc1=0000FF&amp;t=folthenewyory-20&amp;o=1&amp;p=8&amp;l=as4&amp;m=amazon&amp;f=ifr&amp;ref=ss_til&amp;asins=B001QJQWG0" style="width:120px;height:240px;" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe><iframe src="http://rcm.amazon.com/e/cm?lt1=_blank&amp;bc1=000000&amp;IS2=1&amp;bg1=FFFFFF&amp;fc1=000000&amp;lc1=0000FF&amp;t=folthenewyory-20&amp;o=1&amp;p=8&amp;l=as4&amp;m=amazon&amp;f=ifr&amp;ref=ss_til&amp;asins=B001A0ZT2I" style="width:120px;height:240px;" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe><br /><br /></div></div></div><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4492444098437691579-8864764278183440525?l=home-exercise-equipment.blogspot.com' alt='' /></div>
<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/IwN6thCHimUuwtiWABkdVWHmc88/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/IwN6thCHimUuwtiWABkdVWHmc88/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/IwN6thCHimUuwtiWABkdVWHmc88/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/IwN6thCHimUuwtiWABkdVWHmc88/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HomeExerciseEquipmentReviewsAndTips/~4/l4o2OttLxIc" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
